						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken stone built into the wall of the Taluk-office.</hi></p>						

						<p>Srīvallabha—undated.</p>						

						<p>This record is not dated but is assigned to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 793</hi> by Dr. Fleet who has edited it in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. VI, pp. 163 ff.</p>						

						<p>It refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Srīvallabha</hi> and records a grant in the form of proportionate quantity of the goods turned out by the weavers. The grant was made by the headman of the guild of the weavers of <hi rend="italic">nūruṁkēri</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Purigere</hi> <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> the present Lakshmēs11var.</p>						

						</summary>
